Unendorsed riders account for just 14% of the total number of motorcyclists on our roads, but they are involved in nearly half the crashes. So get trained and get endorsed.
Across Michigan, 38,000 riders are still not endorsed, and that matters...

Motorcycle safety involves so many factors, but riders can shift the odds in their favor by: 1. Getting trained. 2. Going through the process of getting a CYCLE endorsement on your license. 3. Wearing the right gear.

Whether you’re riding a two-wheeled vehicle or three-wheeled one, our message is the same:  Get trained before you ride. You can find training courses online at https://t.co/ctsPzil1RV. There’s even a basic course for three-wheeled bikes. https://t.co/KXK5u873Yh
Older riders are disproportionately involved in crashes so training and the license endorsement is key to avoid them. It’s not just young people.
